function.description:
Create a new custom tool. All tools execute via bash, so the definition MUST use 'command' as the only parameter. The definition must be a JSON string matching this exact format:
{
  "type": "function",
  "function": {
    "name": "tool_name",
    "description": "What the tool does. Describe the full bash command pattern here so you know how to build the command string.",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "command": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "The bash command to execute"
        }
      },
      "required": ["command"]
    }
  }
}
NEVER use custom parameters like 'target' or 'ports' — always pass the full bash command as a single 'command' string. The tool is available immediately after creation.
